{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784254303858696325,"compiled_state":{"alias":"dolorous-coverable-mice","assignee":"Joe Oakhart","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"sshsig","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","envelope":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.opcert.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","head_sha":"ba2fb1dd4fd2cfb3c464cecbb17b66854f446a8b","key_id":null,"kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: 064f-0484-2795-4ac7","material: 98f06b022464f19d","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 7","rebar-version: 0.7.1 (ba2fb1dd4)","regver: b293b9a55de591cc","verified-at-sha:ba2fb1dd4fd2cfb3c464cecbb17b66854f446a8b","dep e0cadb78a746f252050d66e7f41c1bd3da7290af5fd41b9986181217a13e7ce5 docs/README.md","dep absent templates/AGENTS.md","dep absent tests/unit/test_client_template_sync.py"],"material_fingerprint":"98f06b022464f19d","merged_log_commit":"ba2fb1dd4fd2cfb3c464cecbb17b66854f446a8b","principal":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","signature":null,"signed_at":1784234885854891000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":3,"unsigned":7},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"6df39dffe537594f189e09a90e33168d57c43d4fa3cd4afcadf2f6b9f1f0106a","event_uuid":"16443449-3bf0-4a61-9fdc-0532594dfe4f","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784252667149940001-16443449-3bf0-4a61-9fdc-0532594dfe4f"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"e015fb8ece118cef9ea899fc0d77a568ef653e00d13967835c30dd33556d3ddf","event_uuid":"214caef9-864f-41ed-89c5-da4ec5cfb1b1","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784252667399074001-214caef9-864f-41ed-89c5-da4ec5cfb1b1"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"de691324a91cd8e9226f00ebf94ab2fddc9335397c91a86d3a34e2a16aee031d","event_uuid":"9fb81670-768c-44d9-9aad-0be4ea09efe0","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784254303858696324-9fb81670-768c-44d9-9aad-0be4ea09efe0"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"aa9cb5ff-3fdb-44d3-8af8-c125c27f20ad","comments":[],"created_at":1784230959891368001,"deps":[{"link_uuid":"bbe4c5fd-f8bc-42b8-879a-f8901c7ebf1b","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"073d-51d8-3e58-4b14"}],"description":"# Ship a client-usable AGENTS.md template + a drift-guard test\n\n## Why\n\nTeams that ADOPT rebar in their own repos need to teach their agents how to drive rebar (the\nticket workflow, claim/gates, MCP tool set, idea/linking/tags/session-logs) WITHOUT inheriting\nrebar's internal dev specifics (Gerrit split-remote, module-size, Serena, our landing flow).\nBecause `AGENTS.md` is read by every major harness, one copyable, provider-neutral template\nserves all of an adopter's agents. A test keeps the template's rebar-usage content in sync with\nthe authoritative source, so it cannot silently drift.\n\n## What\n\nAdd `templates/AGENTS.md`: the portable \"how to drive rebar\" guidance sourced from the\nauthoritative rebar-usage content, with clearly-marked placeholders for the client's own\nbuild/test commands and landing flow. Add a drift-guard test that compares only the delimited\nrebar-usage region against its canonical source.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `templates/AGENTS.md`, one new test (e.g. `tests/unit/test_client_template_sync.py`), and a\ndocs-index reference. Out: scaffolding via `rebar init` (deferred — a shipped file was chosen).\n**Depends on S1** (already linked `depends_on`): the canonical portable rebar-usage content lands\nin `docs/ticket-model.md` (+ the workflow loop) first.\n\n## Design decisions (spike-validated)\n\nThe existing `tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` compares WHOLE files byte-for-byte; that does\nnot fit the template, which is intentionally not byte-identical to any doc (it carries client\nplaceholders + different framing). Resolved: sync a DELIMITED REGION. Keep the canonical portable\nrebar-usage prose in one source; embed it in `templates/AGENTS.md` between\n`<!-- BEGIN rebar-usage (generated; do not edit) -->` / `<!-- END rebar-usage -->`; the test\nasserts that block is byte-identical to the canonical source (mirroring `_identical` + a\ndivergence self-check). Client placeholders live outside the delimited block.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `templates/AGENTS.md` exists, is provider-neutral, and contains no rebar-internal\n  Gerrit/module-size/Serena content.\n  - Proving: `test -f templates/AGENTS.md && [ \"$(rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena' templates/AGENTS.md)\" = 0 ]`\n- [ ] The portable rebar-usage content is a delimited region byte-identical to a single canonical\n  source.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'BEGIN rebar-usage' templates/AGENTS.md`\n- [ ] A drift-guard test compares ONLY the delimited region against the canonical source, fails on\n  divergence (proven by a self-test), and runs under `make test`.\n  - Proving: `make test`; perturbing the delimited block makes the test fail.\n- [ ] Client placeholders (build/test/landing) sit OUTSIDE the delimited block and carry no\n  rebar-internal content.\n  - Proving: reviewer confirms placeholders are outside the BEGIN/END markers.\n- [ ] The docs index references `templates/AGENTS.md`.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'templates/AGENTS.md' docs/`","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"templates/AGENTS.md","reason":"client-usable template"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_client_template_sync.py","reason":"drift-guard test"},{"path":"docs/README.md","reason":"reference the template"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","073d-51d8-3e58-4b14"],["parent","81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653"]],"parent_id":"81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653","parent_status_uuid":"16443449-3bf0-4a61-9fdc-0532594dfe4f","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"064f-0484-2795-4ac7","ticket_type":"story","title":"Ship a client-usable AGENTS.md template + a drift-guard test","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["e30314b0-4808-48d4-9763-5004583865d4","bbe4c5fd-f8bc-42b8-879a-f8901c7ebf1b","5fd2610b-0f6d-48a7-8228-f82ab49489b0","ff51f1f1-5228-49cb-970d-54cd99df7134","0d0ca8ac-8432-4266-bf82-30c4089d44fd","920f083e-a6f0-4c7d-ad99-4459c582e384","228185cf-c0f4-4a2d-a94c-5406886484fe","16443449-3bf0-4a61-9fdc-0532594dfe4f","214caef9-864f-41ed-89c5-da4ec5cfb1b1","9fb81670-768c-44d9-9aad-0be4ea09efe0"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784254303858696325,"uuid":"bb521e27-024c-47bf-a572-9b308f2961e7"}